text=%3c%3c|Macropedia/ImperiumEquipmentIndex|>>%0a%0a!! Poly-Control Slave System%0a%0aDuring the [[ImperiumMacropediaTimeline#EarlyImperium|Early Imperium]] PCSs were the dominant form of advanced military hardware control.%0a%0aPCSs allow for multiple controllers to join forces, often this is applied directly to vehicle operations with vehicles that can merge to form larger entities.%0a%0aThe primary benefit is shifting comman burden. The example situation is as follows:%0a%0aTwo tanks are on the battlefield. One is partially disabled, possibly immobilized. Normally, this spells the doom of the tank. However, if the tanks are of similar specie and equipped with PCSs. The unscathed tank can link with it. The commander of the injured tank is then able to focus on repairing his vehicle while the commander of the other tank gains joint fire control and can use his engines to move them if necessary.%0a%0aStatistics from the field indicated that this type of control was much more effective off the ground (in air, sea, or space) combat. However, it was a slight advantage over systems without the capability.%0a%0a!! Fading Glory%0a%0aPCSs started to fade from the battlefield as Telefreiber perfected their swarm dynamic technologies during the later [[ImperiumMacropediaTimeline#HighImperium|High Imperium]]. PCSs were not as adaptable to the shifting, subtle battlefields of the GrandReforms era.%0a%0aThis is not to say that they are not used today. Indeed, public transportation systems are replete with PCSs. %0a%0a!! References%0a# GrandReforms%0a# First Phantom Entry%0a# Second Phantom Entry%0a%0a!! Related Articles%0a(:pagelist group=Macropedia fmt=simple {$Name}:)%0a%0a%0a[[!ImperiumEquipment]] [[!BorisHelfsteinAuthored]] [[!Miscellaneous Equipment]]
